# Project invariants

`epublatejs` is a static SPA that translates ePubs entirely in the
browser. `AGENTS.md` is the long-form charter; this rule is the
on-every-turn checklist.

- **Local-first.** The only network call is to the user-configured
  OpenAI-compatible LLM endpoint. No telemetry, analytics, CDN ping,
  error reporter, or autoupdate. API keys live in IndexedDB on this
  device.
- **Format preservation.** ePub round-trip is byte-equivalent. Inline
  markup is placeholderized as `[[T0]]…[[/T0]]` so the LLM never sees
  raw HTML/XML. Validators in `src/formats/epub/validators.ts` reject
  any reassembly that can't round-trip — don't bypass them.
- **Glossary consistency.** Locked terms are *hard-fail*; target-only
  entries are *soft-locked* (flagged, not auto-rejected). Aliases match
  on word boundaries; particle suffixes round-trip
  (`Saito-san` ↔ `Saito-さん`).
- **Resumability.** Every batch operation persists per-segment state.
  Closing the tab is harmless: re-opening picks up at `pending` /
  `flagged`. Don't store work-in-progress only in React state.
- **OpenAI-compatible only.** All LLM traffic goes through
  `LLMProvider` (`src/llm/base.ts`). Every call is recorded in
  `llm_calls`. Don't widen the provider surface.
- **No silent data loss.** Bumping a Dexie schema means a `.version(N)`
  upgrade with an explicit migration. Never wipe a user's data
  without consent.

When in doubt: smaller, audited changes that preserve resumability and
round-trip identity beat clever ones.
